dataqual.logic: This parcel layer contains discrete, non-overlapping polygons for each property. Adjacent polygons with common ownership and a single tax record have been retained in the "OthLeg" layer that accompanies this TaxPar layer, and dissolved into single parcels in this TaxPar layer. Some non-adjacent parcels may be represented by multi-part polygons where they share common ownership and a single tax record. Public rights-of-way (ROWs) exist as polygons, not null space. Linework associated with private ROWs are retained in the "OthLeg" layer. Water polygons also representing parcel boundaries have been retained in this TaxPar layer. Additional water features that are not considered parcel boundaries may have been placed in the "Misc" layer that accompanies this TaxPar layer. Easements and other similar non-fee taxable boundaries exist in the 'OthLeg" layer, not the TaxPar layer. Unique to Nantucket is the presence of a secondary LOC_ID field... LOC_ID_ISL. This field contains the LOC_ID value in Massachusetts Stateplane Island Feet instead of Mainland coordinates. It has been retained with the expectation that the town of Nantucket will incorporate this ID in their CAMA, and therefore it will faciliate linking exercises with the assessor records.

horizpa.horizpar: Data compiled or reviewed for horizontal accuracy over the MassGIS color orthos from 2008/2009; these orthos are known to be +/- 10' horizontal; however, this data set cannot be used to reach authoritative conclusions about the horizontal accuracy of the boundaries depicted. That work requires a licensed land surveyor.

srcinfo.srccontr: This GIS dataset represents a digital version of assessor tax maps that were previously converted and processed into a GIS file which is used to produce the paper Tax Maps for the community. Original mapping compiled existing paper tax maps.

procstep.procdesc: Parcel polygons and water, wetland and ROW lines converted with ESRI tools to project, dissolve, copy, calculate, and generally manipulate the ESRI version of the data to meet Mass GIS Level III standards. The source data is not changed by this process.

overview.dsoverv: M197TaxPar represents a version of digital municipal parcels for the community of NANTUCKET that is considered ‘level 3’ compliant per the specifications outlined in the MassGIS Standard for Digital Parcel Files. Its features can be linked in a GIS or database environment to a set of standardized assessing attributes in the table M197Assess by using the unique identifying values in the LOC_ID field. This data is also intended to be used in conjunction with associated (and optional) features in the ancillary data layers M197OthLeg and M197Misc. As one of the data sets identified by Massachusetts’ Strategic Plan for Spatial Data Infrastructure (http:/ /www.mass.gov/mgis/stratplan.html), this data enters the public domain as a valuable resource for mapping, planning, and analysis at all levels of government as well as the private sector.
